# Compiled WebAssembly artifacts. These are BUILD OUTPUT, not source: `crates/dmtap-sync-wasm/
# build.sh` produces the browser ones and `build-abi.sh` the raw-ABI module the Go binding embeds.
# Committing them once already cost a real bug — a stale checked-in module kept aborting on free
# long after the source it was built from had been fixed, because nothing ties a binary blob in git
# to the code that produced it. Generating them at build time makes that class of drift impossible.
crates/dmtap-sync-wasm/pkg/
crates/dmtap-sync-wasm/pkg-node/
bindings/go/dmtap_sync_abi.wasm
